%I A316200 #14 Jun 27 2026 23:10:25
%S A316200 0,0,0,2,2,10,15,124,352,2378,9883,63556,313726,1970548,10693249,
%T A316200 66850339,384547086,2411380580
%N A316200 Number of self-avoiding polygons with perimeter n and sides = 1 that have vertex angles from the set 0, +-Pi/5, +-2*Pi/5, +-3*Pi/5, +-4*Pi/5, not counting rotations and reflections as distinct.
%C A316200 Holes are excluded; i.e., the boundary path may nowhere touch or intersect itself.
%C A316200 Also number of free simple matchstick polygons with perimeter n on the cyclotomic ring Z[zeta_10]. - _Anton Pirogov_, Jun 22 2026
%H A316200 Contest Organizers, <a href="http://www.recmath.org/contest/Snakes/index.php">Al Zimmermann's Programming Contests - Snakes on a Plane</a>, Fall 2006.
%H A316200 Hugo Pfoertner, <a href="http://www.randomwalk.de/sequences/a316200.htm">Illustration of polygons of perimeter <= 9</a>.
%H A316200 Anton Pirogov, <a href="https://github.com/apirogov/tilezz">tilezz</a> (exact cyclotomic geometry library including a polygon enumerator).
%H A316200 Anton Pirogov, <a href="https://ratdb.app.pirogov.de">Rat Explorer</a> (interactive database of cyclotomic matchstick polygons).
%H A316200 Anton Pirogov, <a href="https://github.com/apirogov/tilezz-ratdb">RatDB datasets</a> (reproducible datasets containing the enumerated polygons).
%Y A316200 Cf. A258206, A266549, A284869, A306180, A316192, A316195, A316197, A316198, A316199, A316201.
